Description: Convex ring foot and wall sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery skyphos, typ A; wholly glazed save for resting surface and underside, which has a dot and two rings at centre; deltoid graffito cut on underside.
Curator's comments: Compare: The Athenian Agora, vol. xii, no. 340, pl. 16; no. 342, fig. 4, pl. 16.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 380) (Dedications to Apollo)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1286)
